Hello,

&gt; Is is possible to contol crawl order , link etc in H3?

There are a few ways of affecting the order that urls are crawled in. One
thing you can do is mark a url as a prerequisite of another. For more
advanced and
highly
 customizable crawl ordering, you can use a custom QueuePrecedencePolicy to
prioritize queues based on arbitrary criteria, and a UriPrecedencePolicy to
prioritize urls within each queue.

&gt; If I configure two jobs feeding them same url then how do I prevent
heritrixfrom downloading the same content?

You would have to implement a custom alreadySeen check that uses some sort
of centralized database.
This doesn&#39;t directly address your question but you
 might
 also
want to look at
https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Multiple+Machine+Crawling

This is another case where it might be helpful to step back and explain
more broadly what you&#39;re trying to accomplish, so people
can offer
 more practical advice.

Noah



